Planetary Formation
-----------------

===========
  Steps:
===========
Galaxy
	1) Define the location of a supermassive black hole (center)
Star Clusters
Solar System
Stars
Planets
Minor Planets
Satellites
Nebulae
Black Holes
Gamma-ray burst

Most galaxies are 1,000 to 100,000 parsecs in diameter
Observational data suggests that supermassive black holes may exist at the center of many, if not all, galaxies.
Although it is not yet well understood, dark matter appears to account for around 90% of the mass of most galaxies.
